# CostSage robots.txt — Phase-1 SEO/AEO/GEO policy
# Proposed: 2026-04-27
# Resolves audit finding F1 (R1 Option B: allow grounding, opt out of training)
#
# Policy summary:
# - Search crawlers: full access.
# - LLM grounding/RAG bots (ClaudeBot, GPTBot, PerplexityBot, etc.): full access.
# - LLM training corpora (Common Crawl bulk, Bytespider, Amazonbot, etc.): blocked.
# - Cloudflare Content-Signal: search=yes, ai-input=yes, ai-train=no.
#
# Rationale: site must be retrievable by answer engines for AEO + GEO motion to
# function. Training opt-out preserves a defensible posture. See
# clients/costsage/seo-geo-aeo/phase-1-live-audit.md §6 R1.

# Cloudflare Content-Signal preamble (legally meaningful under EU DSM Art. 4)
User-agent: *
Content-Signal: search=yes,ai-input=yes,ai-train=no
Allow: /

# --- LLM grounding / answer-engine bots: ALLOW ---
User-agent: ClaudeBot
Allow: /

User-agent: ChatGPT-User
Allow: /

User-agent: OAI-SearchBot
Allow: /

User-agent: GPTBot
Allow: /

User-agent: PerplexityBot
Allow: /

User-agent: Perplexity-User
Allow: /

User-agent: Google-Extended
Allow: /

User-agent: Applebot
Allow: /

User-agent: Applebot-Extended
Allow: /

User-agent: Bingbot
Allow: /

User-agent: DuckDuckBot
Allow: /

# --- Bulk-training crawlers: BLOCK ---
User-agent: CCBot
Disallow: /

User-agent: Amazonbot
Disallow: /

User-agent: Bytespider
Disallow: /

User-agent: meta-externalagent
Disallow: /

User-agent: FacebookBot
Disallow: /

